Question: What improvements would you like to see in these cultural funding programs?

Response ID: resp_3518
Response Text: The people/groups who get the grants vs the people who don’t, and why that is. Also, more scrutiny / guidelines on how the money is spent on the backend by the bands or nonprofits who get the money. Clearer communication as to who is getting what money and why they are getting it instead of someone else. Also, less money per person, given to more people. Potential idea: the city becomes involved as a collaborator in the project as a stipulation for receiving the fund (for large funds) to help ensure efficiency and equity of spending, and that the project is in some way benefitting Austin more largely from a Culture, Music, or Entertainment frame. 

Consider having a large, rotating pool of advisors who are full time creative workers to refer to in decision making. Of course they would likely be ineligible to receive grant funds if they are also serving in an advisory role to the city, but I know many people (myself included) who would happily forego the chance at grant funds in order to better serve the city with insights “from the ground floor” so to speak

